translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah's day had started uneventful enough."
    new "Sarah's day had started uneventful enough."

    old "Memories of her encounter with Alaric plagued her constantly."
    new "Memories of her encounter with Alaric plagued her constantly."

    old "She had always been in control of her own mind, but now she found it often wandering, whether she wanted to or not."
    new "She had always been in control of her own mind, but now she found it often wandering, whether she wanted to or not."

    old "Sarah shook her head, trying to clear it."
    new "Sarah shook her head, trying to clear it."

    old "Samayra had gotten up surprisingly early."
    new "Samayra had gotten up surprisingly early."

    old "She'd recently taken to starting a garden, and the house had, as always, provided or as much."
    new "She'd recently taken to starting a garden, and the house had, as always, provided or as much."

    old "Working the garden seemed to somehow transform her."
    new "Working the garden seemed to somehow transform her."

    old "The otherwise dainty and frail girl, dug her hands deep into the soil and pulled out the roots with surprising strength."
    new "The otherwise dainty and frail girl, dug her hands deep into the soil and pulled out the roots with surprising strength."

    old "Sarah was happy for her to have a distraction."
    new "Sarah was happy for her to have a distraction."

    old "The house echoed as she walked through it."
    new "The house echoed as she walked through it."

    old "Other than Metis, who kept to his own odd pace, there wasn't anyone."
    new "Other than Metis, who kept to his own odd pace, there wasn't anyone."

    old "She gathered up some strewn about books and documents and began sorting them."
    new "She gathered up some strewn about books and documents and began sorting them."

    old "Sarah had gotten into the habit of simply leaving whatever she was reading on the desk."
    new "Sarah had gotten into the habit of simply leaving whatever she was reading on the desk."

    old "Over time, the pile grew and grew."
    new "Over time, the pile grew and grew."

    old "Seeing the pile reminded her of the mess that Xan would usually leave behind."
    new "Seeing the pile reminded her of the mess that Xan would usually leave behind."

    old "More alike than she might have liked to admit."
    new "More alike than she might have liked to admit."

    old "Still, all of it was mostly a distraction, because in the afternoon, she'd have her first lessen with Metis."
    new "Still, all of it was mostly a distraction, because in the afternoon, she'd have her first lessen with Metis."

    old "He had offered to teach her a variety of magics."
    new "He had offered to teach her a variety of magics."

    old "Sarah had decided on Botany."
    new "Sarah had decided on Botany."

    old "One of the essential skills any mage should have."
    new "One of the essential skills any mage should have."

    old "Sarah had always liked plants and flowers, so the skill seemed like a natural fit."
    new "Sarah had always liked plants and flowers, so the skill seemed like a natural fit."

    old "Sarah had decided on Transmogrification."
    new "Sarah had decided on Transmogrification."

    old "It was a solid skill that most any decent mage should know."
    new "It was a solid skill that most any decent mage should know."

    old "Without a mentor, it would have taken her a lot longer to teach it to herself."
    new "Without a mentor, it would have taken her a lot longer to teach it to herself."

    old "Sarah had decided on Daemonology."
    new "Sarah had decided on Daemonology."

    old "It was the most dangerous out of all that he had offered. But at the same time, Sarah had found it the most appealing."
    new "It was the most dangerous out of all that he had offered. But at the same time, Sarah had found it the most appealing."

    old "Or perhaps that was because it was the most dangerous."
    new "Or perhaps that was because it was the most dangerous."

    old "Though she looked forward to learning a new skill, Sarah wasn't all to sure what to make of the man himself."
    new "Though she looked forward to learning a new skill, Sarah wasn't all to sure what to make of the man himself."

    old "Something about him continued to seem strange to her."
    new "Something about him continued to seem strange to her."

    old "Unsure, Sarah arrived at the study room later that afternoon."
    new "Unsure, Sarah arrived at the study room later that afternoon."

    old "She saw Metis already sitting at one of the desks, hunched over a text."
    new "She saw Metis already sitting at one of the desks, hunched over a text."

    old "He turned around seemingly startled."
    new "He turned around seemingly startled."

    old "Ooh, hey there Sarah. I didn't see you come in."
    new "Ooh, hey there Sarah. I didn't see you come in."

    old "Sarah walked further into the room."
    new "Sarah walked further into the room."

    old "She hadn't used this room...not since Xan."
    new "She hadn't used this room...not since Xan."

    old "So, you're ready to get started?"
    new "So, you're ready to get started?"

    old "Excellent. Well, we can start with the basics."
    new "Excellent. Well, we can start with the basics."

    old "Botany is considered one of the pillars of any good mage apprenticeship."
    new "Botany is considered one of the pillars of any good mage apprenticeship."

    old "Not all plants contain the potential for magical use, but those that do can have immense effects."
    new "Not all plants contain the potential for magical use, but those that do can have immense effects."

    old "Some are used for altering spells, used in complex rituals, or to heighten one's own potential."
    new "Some are used for altering spells, used in complex rituals, or to heighten one's own potential."

    old "Sarah nodded along as he continued to explain."
    new "Sarah nodded along as he continued to explain."

    old "In front of her were some books, all selected for study by Metis."
    new "In front of her were some books, all selected for study by Metis."

    old "Now while the use and application of these plants is mostly a matter of study, we will focus on the topic of cultivation."
    new "Now while the use and application of these plants is mostly a matter of study, we will focus on the topic of cultivation."

    old "Cultivation?"
    new "Cultivation?"

    old "Yes. The most important plants for a mage do not naturally occur in nature."
    new "Yes. The most important plants for a mage do not naturally occur in nature."

    old "They are instead grown by combining the basics of growing plants, with magical infusion."
    new "They are instead grown by combining the basics of growing plants, with magical infusion."

    old "Sarah frowned. She'd never heard of that before."
    new "Sarah frowned. She'd never heard of that before."

    old "As mages, we can introduce magical energies into plants during early stages of their development."
    new "As mages, we can introduce magical energies into plants during early stages of their development."

    old "Done properly, this can guide the evolution of a plant along radical new lines, drawing out new properties for use in, for example, potions."
    new "Done properly, this can guide the evolution of a plant along radical new lines, drawing out new properties for use in, for example, potions."

    old "And what if done improperly?"
    new "And what if done improperly?"

    old "Well, most often an improper application of infusion will result in the plant dying."
    new "Well, most often an improper application of infusion will result in the plant dying."

    old "The most common mistake tends to be supplying either too much magic, drowning out the plant's natural elements, or too little, bearing no effect."
    new "The most common mistake tends to be supplying either too much magic, drowning out the plant's natural elements, or too little, bearing no effect."

    old "The real art of magical botany is to fine and feel the balancing point."
    new "The real art of magical botany is to fine and feel the balancing point."

    old "Sarah looked at him as he continued to explain."
    new "Sarah looked at him as he continued to explain."

    old "It began to sound more challenging than she had initially expected."
    new "It began to sound more challenging than she had initially expected."

    old "For nearly an hour, Metis continued taking her through all the basics. What kinds of plants were useful. How to infuse a seedling. On and on."
    new "For nearly an hour, Metis continued taking her through all the basics. What kinds of plants were useful. How to infuse a seedling. On and on."

    old "Finally, he produced two pots."
    new "Finally, he produced two pots."

    old "Well, enough talking. Talking was always more Xan's thing. I like to get our hands dirty."
    new "Well, enough talking. Talking was always more Xan's thing. I like to get our hands dirty."

    old "He placed one of the pots in front of her."
    new "He placed one of the pots in front of her."

    old "So, there is a seedling in here."
    new "So, there is a seedling in here."

    old "Let's give it a good try. Just do as I do."
    new "Let's give it a good try. Just do as I do."

    old "Sarah watched intently as Metis weaved his hands near his own pot. Sarah could spot the faint traces of magical energy, entering the seed."
    new "Sarah watched intently as Metis weaved his hands near his own pot. Sarah could spot the faint traces of magical energy, entering the seed."

    old "It was subtle, easy to miss if she didn't know what to look for."
    new "It was subtle, easy to miss if she didn't know what to look for."

    old "And that's it."
    new "And that's it."

    old "Really? Just that?"
    new "Really? Just that?"

    old "Yes. If I did everything right, this rose will grow into a Whisper-Rose."
    new "Yes. If I did everything right, this rose will grow into a Whisper-Rose."

    old "Whisper-Rose?"
    new "Whisper-Rose?"

    old "Yes. They are very attuned to the sounds of their surroundings and with the proper spell, can reproduce everything they heard."
    new "Yes. They are very attuned to the sounds of their surroundings and with the proper spell, can reproduce everything they heard."

    old "That's...not..."
    new "That's...not..."

    old "Possible?"
    new "Possible?"

    old "Ooh Sarah, so much of what you can do seems impossible to common folk. You think this is somehow too much?"
    new "Ooh Sarah, so much of what you can do seems impossible to common folk. You think this is somehow too much?"

    old "Sarah suddenly became aware of just how little she knew about the magical world."
    new "Sarah suddenly became aware of just how little she knew about the magical world."

    old "Now go ahead, you give it a try."
    new "Now go ahead, you give it a try."

    old "Sarah placed her hand near the pot."
    new "Sarah placed her hand near the pot."

    old "Weaving her fingers, she gently produced and guided the magical energies into the seedling."
    new "Weaving her fingers, she gently produced and guided the magical energies into the seedling."

    old "Way too much. You're drowning it. It needs to be more subtle."
    new "Way too much. You're drowning it. It needs to be more subtle."

    old "I thought I was being subtle."
    new "I thought I was being subtle."

    old "You were, if you were weaving a spell. But these seedlings, they're incredibly delicate."
    new "You were, if you were weaving a spell. But these seedlings, they're incredibly delicate."

    old "Here, try again."
    new "Here, try again."

    old "Metis placed a new pot in front of her."
    new "Metis placed a new pot in front of her."

    old "Again, Sarah began to weave, straining her attention as she did her best to hold back, releasing only fractions of magical energy."
    new "Again, Sarah began to weave, straining her attention as she did her best to hold back, releasing only fractions of magical energy."

    old "A bit more, this time."
    new "A bit more, this time."

    old "Sarah narrowed her eyes and began to add more."
    new "Sarah narrowed her eyes and began to add more."

    old "Metis suddenly reached out and grabbed the pot, pulling it away."
    new "Metis suddenly reached out and grabbed the pot, pulling it away."

    old "A decent attempt, but this one...I'll give it half a chance of surviving."
    new "A decent attempt, but this one...I'll give it half a chance of surviving."

    old "Let's keep trying. You're getting the hang of it."
    new "Let's keep trying. You're getting the hang of it."

    old "Pot after pot. Seedling after seedling."
    new "Pot after pot. Seedling after seedling."

    old "Sarah spend countless hours, her attention fully focussed, weaving differing degrees of magical energy into the seedlings."
    new "Sarah spend countless hours, her attention fully focussed, weaving differing degrees of magical energy into the seedlings."

    old "Hoping to produce at least one that might sprout into a magical plant."
    new "Hoping to produce at least one that might sprout into a magical plant."

    old "Near the end, the room was littered in pots. Varying degrees of hopefulness."
    new "Near the end, the room was littered in pots. Varying degrees of hopefulness."

    old "Metis walked around, drawing numbers on the pots as he went by them."
    new "Metis walked around, drawing numbers on the pots as he went by them."

    old "We'll need to see how each of these turn out."
    new "We'll need to see how each of these turn out."

    old "You think any of them will sprout?"
    new "You think any of them will sprout?"

    old "More than a few I imagine, you were getting the hang of it near the end."
    new "More than a few I imagine, you were getting the hang of it near the end."

    old "But it's always a waiting game."
    new "But it's always a waiting game."

    old "Sarah nodded. She felt proud enough about her achievement."
    new "Sarah nodded. She felt proud enough about her achievement."

    old "Are they all the same?"
    new "Are they all the same?"

    old "The seeds? Ooh no, certainly not."
    new "The seeds? Ooh no, certainly not."

    old "Just grabbed a handful out of Xan's old stock. Differing sizes, types. That makes for good practice."
    new "Just grabbed a handful out of Xan's old stock. Differing sizes, types. That makes for good practice."

    old "So how do we know what they're gonna turn into?"
    new "So how do we know what they're gonna turn into?"

    old "Metis smiled."
    new "Metis smiled."

    old "Well I suppose that's half the fun, isn't it? Magical botany is nothing if not surprising."
    new "Well I suppose that's half the fun, isn't it? Magical botany is nothing if not surprising."

    old "For now, I suggest you give these some time to grow. Take the time in between to study these books."
    new "For now, I suggest you give these some time to grow. Take the time in between to study these books."

    old "Metis gestured towards the pile he had laid out for her."
    new "Metis gestured towards the pile he had laid out for her."

    old "Sarah grabbed the books under her arm."
    new "Sarah grabbed the books under her arm."

    old "How long are these going to take?"
    new "How long are these going to take?"

    old "Magical plants tend to grow a lot faster, but who can tell. I'll let you know when the first batch is ready."
    new "Magical plants tend to grow a lot faster, but who can tell. I'll let you know when the first batch is ready."

    old "Sarah nodded and turned to leave."
    new "Sarah nodded and turned to leave."

    old "Her first day of practical study completed, she set in for a long night of actual studying."
    new "Her first day of practical study completed, she set in for a long night of actual studying."

    old "Transmogrification is considered one of the base skills for any mage."
    new "Transmogrification is considered one of the base skills for any mage."

    old "Though considered a base skill, it's actually a rather challenging one; not without risk."
    new "Though considered a base skill, it's actually a rather challenging one; not without risk."

    old "What risks are those?"
    new "What risks are those?"

    old "Metis leaned against the desk."
    new "Metis leaned against the desk."

    old "Well, you're changing your body, altering its composition."
    new "Well, you're changing your body, altering its composition."

    old "For example, you could change your body to take on the shape of a wolf, but the truth is you don't really want that."
    new "For example, you could change your body to take on the shape of a wolf, but the truth is you don't really want that."

    old "Well if you truly shifted yourself into such a form, you would entirely become it."
    new "Well if you truly shifted yourself into such a form, you would entirely become it."

    old "Even your mind, your intellect, would become animalistic."
    new "Even your mind, your intellect, would become animalistic."

    old "And once you reach a state like that...how do you get back?"
    new "And once you reach a state like that...how do you get back?"

    old "Sarah shivered. Trapped in an animal form forever sounded like a nightmare."
    new "Sarah shivered. Trapped in an animal form forever sounded like a nightmare."

    old "You mean...I could be trapped like that forever if I mess up?"
    new "You mean...I could be trapped like that forever if I mess up?"

    old "Metis shook his head."
    new "Metis shook his head."

    old "No, that's actually quite rare."
    new "No, that's actually quite rare."

    old "Even when you entirely transform, the soul seems to have a way of restoring itself to its base nature."
    new "Even when you entirely transform, the soul seems to have a way of restoring itself to its base nature."

    old "Even unconsciously, there seems to be an urge for a person to return to whatever their true form is."
    new "Even unconsciously, there seems to be an urge for a person to return to whatever their true form is."

    old "But it has happened on occasion, so I think the risk is still important to know."
    new "But it has happened on occasion, so I think the risk is still important to know."

    old "Good that you mentioned it."
    new "Good that you mentioned it."

    old "Metis slapped his hands together, the sound of the clap startled her."
    new "Metis slapped his hands together, the sound of the clap startled her."

    old "Alright, let's kick this off with a good old basic property alteration."
    new "Alright, let's kick this off with a good old basic property alteration."

    old "Property alteration?"
    new "Property alteration?"

    old "Gosh, Xan really has been keeping you back, hasn't he?"
    new "Gosh, Xan really has been keeping you back, hasn't he?"

    old "Property alterations are the most simply form of transmogrification. Basically, altering certain properties of your body."
    new "Property alterations are the most simply form of transmogrification. Basically, altering certain properties of your body."

    old "Metis waved his hands across his body."
    new "Metis waved his hands across his body."

    old "Suddenly, he jumped up..."
    new "Suddenly, he jumped up..."

    old "Then, very slowly, his body drifted back down to the floor."
    new "Then, very slowly, his body drifted back down to the floor."

    old "Altering your body's mass."
    new "Altering your body's mass."

    old "Like this, you can float like a dandelion on a breeze."
    new "Like this, you can float like a dandelion on a breeze."

    old "His feet touched the ground, barely making a sound."
    new "His feet touched the ground, barely making a sound."

    old "That's pretty impressive, but I already know how to levitate."
    new "That's pretty impressive, but I already know how to levitate."

    old "Of course, but this is only the first step. Alternatively, you can increase the mass of your body by a hundred times."
    new "Of course, but this is only the first step. Alternatively, you can increase the mass of your body by a hundred times."

    old "You can make your skin as hard as stone. Transform into a cat and move around unseen."
    new "You can make your skin as hard as stone. Transform into a cat and move around unseen."

    old "Every great field of study begins with a few first steps."
    new "Every great field of study begins with a few first steps."

    old "Alright then, how do I start?"
    new "Alright then, how do I start?"

    old "Simple."
    new "Simple."

    old "Focus yourself on your own body. Close your eyes and really feel your own body. The skin. The organs. The cells."
    new "Focus yourself on your own body. Close your eyes and really feel your own body. The skin. The organs. The cells."

    old "Draw in your mind a pure image of your own body, all that you are, and seperate it from everything outside of yourself."
    new "Draw in your mind a pure image of your own body, all that you are, and seperate it from everything outside of yourself."

    old "Isolate the singular fact of your own body."
    new "Isolate the singular fact of your own body."

    old "Sarah closed her eyes and tried to do as he said."
    new "Sarah closed her eyes and tried to do as he said."

    old "Concentration. Focus. Meditation."
    new "Concentration. Focus. Meditation."

    old "Again and again, she repeated his words in her mind like a mantra."
    new "Again and again, she repeated his words in her mind like a mantra."

    old "And to her own surprise, slowly, in the eye of her own mind, she began to grasp her own body."
    new "And to her own surprise, slowly, in the eye of her own mind, she began to grasp her own body."

    old "Once you see yourself, and only yourself...act on it. Impose your own will, twist nature through the magical energies, no different than casting a spell."
    new "Once you see yourself, and only yourself...act on it. Impose your own will, twist nature through the magical energies, no different than casting a spell."

    old "Only now, you're casting it on yourself."
    new "Only now, you're casting it on yourself."

    old "And she spoke the words, imposing her own will on her body, which she now understood to be little more than an instrument. The shell of her true self."
    new "And she spoke the words, imposing her own will on her body, which she now understood to be little more than an instrument. The shell of her true self."

    old "A shell she could change and manipulate, without altering her own essential self."
    new "A shell she could change and manipulate, without altering her own essential self."

    old "And she watched from the void as her body drifted up, the weight of her own body willed away."
    new "And she watched from the void as her body drifted up, the weight of her own body willed away."

    old "When she opened her eyes again, she saw herself drifting above the ground."
    new "When she opened her eyes again, she saw herself drifting above the ground."

    old "Wow, it actually worked!"
    new "Wow, it actually worked!"

    old "You're a remarkably quick study."
    new "You're a remarkably quick study."

    old "Sarah smiled, surprised even at her own success."
    new "Sarah smiled, surprised even at her own success."

    old "Slowly, without any of her own action, she found herself slowly drifting back to the ground."
    new "Slowly, without any of her own action, she found herself slowly drifting back to the ground."

    old "Why is that happening? Didn't I just will myself to float?"
    new "Why is that happening? Didn't I just will myself to float?"

    old "You did, but as I said earlier, the soul has a way of imposing its own form on your body."
    new "You did, but as I said earlier, the soul has a way of imposing its own form on your body."

    old "Without a constant pressure, your body will adapt back to its natural shape. Like a bubble, it always desires to return to the same form."
    new "Without a constant pressure, your body will adapt back to its natural shape. Like a bubble, it always desires to return to the same form."

    old "This lightness is an aberration, and your body will drive it out over time, unless you keep enforcing it."
    new "This lightness is an aberration, and your body will drive it out over time, unless you keep enforcing it."

    old "Sarah felt her feet touching the ground."
    new "Sarah felt her feet touching the ground."

    old "I see...and that's true of all changes?"
    new "I see...and that's true of all changes?"

    old "Essentially all. It's been known to stick on very rare occasion, but that's hardly something we need to concern ourselves with."
    new "Essentially all. It's been known to stick on very rare occasion, but that's hardly something we need to concern ourselves with."

    old "For now, you should be happy. For just a first lesson, this has been more than impressive."
    new "For now, you should be happy. For just a first lesson, this has been more than impressive."

    old "But don't start letting this get to your head."
    new "But don't start letting this get to your head."

    old "Metis grabbed and pushed a pile of books into her arms."
    new "Metis grabbed and pushed a pile of books into her arms."

    old "Read up on that. Study the basics. Next lesson we can see how fast you can go."
    new "Read up on that. Study the basics. Next lesson we can see how fast you can go."

    old "Daemonology is one of the oldest Arts. Some even believe it to be the very first Art ever learned by a mage."
    new "Daemonology is one of the oldest Arts. Some even believe it to be the very first Art ever learned by a mage."

    old "It's been known under many names over the millenia, but most now refer to this field as Daemonology."
    new "It's been known under many names over the millenia, but most now refer to this field as Daemonology."

    old "Before I continue, I want impress on you that within the Order, not all are as open-minded regarding this field as I am."
    new "Before I continue, I want impress on you that within the Order, not all are as open-minded regarding this field as I am."

    old "Metis leaned against the edge of the table."
    new "Metis leaned against the edge of the table."

    old "Well...did Xan tell you of the history of our Order? The fall of the ancient empire."
    new "Well...did Xan tell you of the history of our Order? The fall of the ancient empire."

    old "He's told enough."
    new "He's told enough."

    old "Well, the very ritual that caused that particular disaster falls within this field of Daemonology."
    new "Well, the very ritual that caused that particular disaster falls within this field of Daemonology."

    old "And so there are those among our order who imagine that this field should be forbidden. They scorn those who research it."
    new "And so there are those among our order who imagine that this field should be forbidden. They scorn those who research it."

    old "Sarah looked at Metis intently."
    new "Sarah looked at Metis intently."

    old "And you don't agree?"
    new "And you don't agree?"

    old "I won't disagree that this magic is dangerous. I just don't agree that it is uniquely dangerous."
    new "I won't disagree that this magic is dangerous. I just don't agree that it is uniquely dangerous."

    old "A fire spell can burn down a city. Some mages can rip apart mountains."
    new "A fire spell can burn down a city. Some mages can rip apart mountains."

    old "Are they not dangerous?"
    new "Are they not dangerous?"

    old "Even without this field, there is enough magic in all the world to burn it down a hundred times over."
    new "Even without this field, there is enough magic in all the world to burn it down a hundred times over."

    old "Suppose we burned down every last city and town. Would that be any less of a disaster than an incursion from some alien world?"
    new "Suppose we burned down every last city and town. Would that be any less of a disaster than an incursion from some alien world?"

    old "Sarah found herself understanding his point of view."
    new "Sarah found herself understanding his point of view."

    old "Besides, I also believe if the greatest danger is from world's beyond our own, then we should not run away from that fact."
    new "Besides, I also believe if the greatest danger is from world's beyond our own, then we should not run away from that fact."

    old "Instead, we should study the source of this danger. If the day ever comes, we might very much need it."
    new "Instead, we should study the source of this danger. If the day ever comes, we might very much need it."

    old "That makes sense...I think."
    new "That makes sense...I think."

    old "I'm glad you think so. Xan was never as open-minded about it. He always chastised me for my interests in this field."
    new "I'm glad you think so. Xan was never as open-minded about it. He always chastised me for my interests in this field."

    old "Speaking of, is that old spirit still drifting about here?"
    new "Speaking of, is that old spirit still drifting about here?"

    old "Yeah, I always enjoyed my conversations with him when I still studied here. Tricky creature that one."
    new "Yeah, I always enjoyed my conversations with him when I still studied here. Tricky creature that one."

    old "But he seems to be avoiding me ever since I've returned."
    new "But he seems to be avoiding me ever since I've returned."

    old "Found a new toy, I suppose."
    new "Found a new toy, I suppose."

    old "He gave her a meaningful look."
    new "He gave her a meaningful look."

    old "I don't know what you're hinting at."
    new "I don't know what you're hinting at."

    old "Metis threw up his hands."
    new "Metis threw up his hands."

    old "I didn't mean anything by it."
    new "I didn't mean anything by it."

    old "He clapped his hands together."
    new "He clapped his hands together."

    old "Enough distraction, let's get into it."
    new "Enough distraction, let's get into it."

    old "Sarah watched as Metis piled more books and reading texts onto her desk."
    new "Sarah watched as Metis piled more books and reading texts onto her desk."

    old "More has been written on this field than you could read in a hundred lifetimes."
